parameters.value:
[Date: Tue, 10 Jan 2023 23:34:54 +0000 (UTC) From: Patients Know Best To: AZ Patient 3 Message-ID: <1212358206.803.1673393694129@8886d02463e2> Subject: You are connected to a new team at EMIS Org name MIME-Version: 1.0 Content-Type: multipart/mixed; boundary="----=_Part_800_2102415052.1673393694125" ------=_Part_800_2102415052.1673393694125 Content-Type: multipart/related; boundary="----=_Part_801_2140409126.1673393694125" ------=_Part_801_2140409126.1673393694125 Content-Type: multipart/alternative; boundary="----=_Part_802_1773108537.1673393694125" ------=_Part_802_1773108537.1673393694125 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit Dear AZ, EMIS Org name has connected your Patients Know Best (PKB) record to a new team that is, or has been, working with you. The team's name is EMIS Team A. Why has this happened? EMIS Team A holds information about you or for you. PKB links you to the team so you can see information about you (such as test results) and information for you (such as library links). In some cases, you can interact with the team (through secure messaging). Your PKB record is a single place to store information from you, your health professionals and your medical devices. To learn more about PKB, please visit our website: http://pkb-frontend-4 What happens next? When you have registered, if EMIS Team A sends you information, PKB will notify you by email. What if I do not know the EMIS Org name or EMIS Team A team? Sometimes you may see an organisation or team name that is unfamiliar to you. This often happens when health care services share resources for managing their patients' or service users' care. For example, GPs and hospitals sometimes share laboratory systems for your test results, and therefore you may receive data from an organisation you've never been to. How do I know what information they have about me and what they can see about me? The information they have about you or for you so far is in your PKB record. You can log in to see it now: http://pkb-frontend-4 This team is able to see information in your record marked with general, social, mental and sexual privacy. You can change the level of access they have at any time by clicking this link (http://pkb-frontend-4/patient/myConsentTeam.action?tab=invitations&subTab=myClinicians) and adjusting their settings, you can read more in the PKB manual (https://manual.patientsknowbest.com/patient/sharing). Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Log into your record to see your medical information and manage your care: http://pkb-frontend-4 Yours, Patients Know Best Help Team w: www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us e: help@pkbtest.com ------=_Part_802_1773108537.1673393694125 Content-Type: text/html;charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Dear AZ,

EMIS Org name has connected your Patients Know Best (PKB) record to a new team that is, or has been, working with you. The team's name is EMIS Team A.

Why has this happened?
EMIS Team A holds information about you or for you. PKB links you to the team so you can see information about you (such as test results) and information for you (such as library links). In some cases, you can interact with the team (through secure messaging).

Your PKB record is a single place to store information from you, your health professionals and your medical devices. To learn more about PKB, please visit our website.

What happens next?
When you have registered, if EMIS Team A sends you information, PKB will notify you by email.

What if I do not know the EMIS Org name or EMIS Team A team?
Sometimes you may see an organisation or team name that is unfamiliar to you. This often happens when health care services share resources for managing their patients' or service users' care. For example, GPs and hospitals sometimes share laboratory systems for your test results, and therefore you may receive data from an organisation you've never been to.

How do I know what information they have about me and what they can see about me?
The information they have about you or for you so far is in your PKB record. You can log in to see it now.

This team is able to see information in your record marked with general, social, mental and sexual privacy.

You can change the level of access they have at any time by clicking this link and adjusting their settings, you can read more in the PKB manual.

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Log into your record to see your medical information and manage your care.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team
